<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="131" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="131">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="131">
When describing 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Sorbus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Sorbus arguta" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arguta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">Sorbus arguta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Yü">Yue</normalizedToken>
designated &quot; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">T. H. Tu 5449</emphasis>
&quot; at PE (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. A holotype of Sorbus guanxianensis Ku (PE 00020830) B holotype of Sorbus arguta T. T. Yu (PE 00934274)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.201.84027.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/708949" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">2B</figureCitation>
) as the holotype (
<bibRefCitation author="Yue, TT" journalOrPublisher="Zhiwu Fenlei Xuebao" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" pagination="202 - 236" publicationUrl="https://www.plantsystematics.com/CN/article/advancedSearchResult.do" refId="B17" refString="Yue, TT, Kuan, KC, 1963. Taxa nova Rosacearum Sinicarum (I). Zhiwu Fenlei Xuebao 8 (3): 202 - 236, https://www.plantsystematics.com/CN/article/advancedSearchResult.do" title="Taxa nova Rosacearum Sinicarum (I)." url="https://www.plantsystematics.com/CN/article/advancedSearchResult.do" volume="8" year="1963">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Yü">Yue</normalizedToken>
and Kuan 1963
</bibRefCitation>
). It was accepted by 
<bibRefCitation author="Yue, TT" editor="Yue, TT" journalOrPublisher="Science Press, Beijing" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" pagination="1 - 344" publicationUrl="http://www.iplant.cn/info/Sorbus?t=foc" refId="B18" refString="Yue, TT, Lu, LT, 1974. Spiraea, Dichotomanthes, Cotoneaster, Sorbus, Chaenomeles. In: Yue, TT, Ed., Flora Republicae Popularis Sinicae 36. Science Press, Beijing: 1 - 344, http://www.iplant.cn/info/Sorbus?t=foc" title="Spiraea, Dichotomanthes, Cotoneaster, Sorbus, Chaenomeles." url="http://www.iplant.cn/info/Sorbus?t=foc" volumeTitle="Flora Republicae Popularis Sinicae 36." year="1974">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Yü">Yue</normalizedToken>
and Lu (1974)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Gabrielian, E" journalOrPublisher="Academy of Sciences of the Armenian SSR, Erevan, USSR" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" refId="B3" refString="Gabrielian, E, 1978. The genus Sorbus L. in Western Asia and the Himalayas. Academy of Sciences of the Armenian SSR, Erevan, USSR" title="The genus Sorbus L. in Western Asia and the Himalayas." year="1978">Gabrielian (1978)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1139/b90-288" author="Phipps, JB" journalOrPublisher="Canadian Journal of Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" pagination="2209 - 2269" refId="B11" refString="Phipps, JB, Robertson, K, Smith, PG, Rohrer, JR, 1990. A checklist of the subfamily Maloideae Rosaceae. Canadian Journal of Botany 68 (10): 2209 - 2269, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1139/b90-288" title="A checklist of the subfamily Maloideae Rosaceae." url="https://doi.org/10.1139/b90-288" volume="68" year="1990">Phipps et al. (1990)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Lu, LT" editor="Wu, ZY" journalOrPublisher="9: Rosaceae. Science Press, Beijing; Missouri Botanical Garden Press, St. Loui" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" pagination="144 - 170" publicationUrl="http://foc.eflora.cn/content" refId="B7" refString="Lu, LT, Spongberg, SA, 2003. Sorbus Linnaeus. In: Wu, ZY, Raven, PH, Hong, DY, Eds., Flora of China, vol. 9: Rosaceae. Science Press, Beijing; Missouri Botanical Garden Press, St. Loui: 144 - 170, http://foc.eflora.cn/content" title="Sorbus Linnaeus." url="http://foc.eflora.cn/content" volumeTitle="Flora of China, vol." year="2003">Lu and Spongberg (2003)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Ohashi, H" journalOrPublisher="Shokubutsu Kenkyu Zasshi" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" pagination="355 - 361" publicationUrl="www.jjbotany.com/pdf/JJB_068_355_361.pdf" refId="B10" refString="Ohashi, H, Iketani, H, 1993. New Combinations of Asiatic Aria (Rosaceae - Maloideae -Sorbeae. Shokubutsu Kenkyu Zasshi 68 (6): 355 - 361, www.jjbotany.com/pdf/JJB_068_355_361.pdf" title="New Combinations of Asiatic Aria (Rosaceae - Maloideae - Sorbeae." url="www.jjbotany.com/pdf/JJB_068_355_361.pdf" volume="68" year="1993">Ohashi and Iketani (1993)</bibRefCitation>
transferred it to genus 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Aria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Aria" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">Aria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and proposed a new name 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. yuarguta" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" rank="species" species="yuarguta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">A. yuarguta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
H. Ohashi et Iketan (Ohashi and Iketan 1993: 361) for 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. arguta" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" rank="species" species="arguta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">A. arguta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
had been already used by Roemer in 1847 for a different species. Mezhenskyj transferred it to 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Micromeles" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Micromeles" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">Micromeles</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Mezhenska, LO" journalOrPublisher="Lira-K, Kiev" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" refId="B9" refString="Mezhenska, LO, Mezhenskyj, VM, Yakubenko, BY, 2018. Collections of fruit and ornamental plants. Lira-K, Kiev" title="Collections of fruit and ornamental plants." year="2018">Mezhenska et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
: 33) and 
<bibRefCitation author="Rushforth, K" journalOrPublisher="Phytologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" pagination="222 - 247" publicationUrl="https://www.phytologia.org/uploads/2/3/4/2/23422706/100_4_222-24" refId="B13" refString="Rushforth, K, 2018. The Whitebeam problem, and a solution. Phytologia 100 (4): 222 - 247, https://www.phytologia.org/uploads/2/3/4/2/23422706/100_4_222-24" title="The Whitebeam problem, and a solution." url="https://www.phytologia.org/uploads/2/3/4/2/23422706/100_4_222-24" volume="100" year="2018">Rushforth (2018</bibRefCitation>
: 241) transferred it to 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Wilsonaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Wilsonaria" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">Wilsonaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="131">
However, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/25027918" author="Aldasoro, JJ" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Botany Monographs" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" pagination="1 - 148" refId="B1" refString="Aldasoro, JJ, Aedo, C, Garmendia, FM, de la Hoz, FP, Navarro, C, 2004. Revision of Sorbus Subgenera Aria and Torminaria (Rosaceae - Maloideae). Systematic Botany Monographs 69: 1 - 148, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/25027918" title="Revision of Sorbus Subgenera Aria and Torminaria (Rosaceae - Maloideae)." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/25027918" volume="69" year="2004">Aldasoro et al. (2004)</bibRefCitation>
argued that: &quot; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. arguta" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" rank="species" species="arguta">S. arguta</taxonomicName>
is a minor variant of 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. megalocarpa" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" rank="species" species="megalocarpa">S. megalocarpa</taxonomicName>
and does not deserve taxonomic recognition
</emphasis>
&quot;, and reduced it to a synonym of the later. A detailed study of the original material showed that 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Sorbus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Sorbus arguta" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arguta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">Sorbus arguta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is obviously different from 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. megalocarpa" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" rank="species" species="megalocarpa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">S. megalocarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Sorbus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Sorbus arguta" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arguta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">Sorbus arguta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has oblong-ovate or ovate-lanceolate leaves with double serrate margins, relatively small corymbs (2-4 cm in diameter) with few flowers, and small sub-globose fruits (1-1.2 cm in diameter) with sparse lenticels, while 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. megalocarpa" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" rank="species" species="megalocarpa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">S. megalocarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has leaves with crenate-serrate margins, large corymbs (10-15 cm in diameter), many flowered (124-258 flowers per inflorescence), and much larger fruits with dense lenticels. Furthermore, 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. arguta" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" rank="species" species="arguta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">S. arguta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
flowers after leaves are unfolded in early May (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Corymbs of Sorbus arguta and S. megalocarpa A flowering specimen of Sorbus arguta (CBDI 0226241) collected by Liang Zhang, Xinmao Zhou and Wenbin Ju, 7 May 2014 B Sorbus megalocarpa at blossoming stage, 21 March 2021 C detail of the inflorescence of S. megalocarpa (B, C were taken by Tailun Hu)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.201.84027.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/708950" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">3A</figureCitation>
, CBDI0226241), whereas 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. megalocarpa" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" rank="species" species="megalocarpa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">S. megalocarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
flowers simultaneously with or before the leaves are unfolded in March (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Corymbs of Sorbus arguta and S. megalocarpa A flowering specimen of Sorbus arguta (CBDI 0226241) collected by Liang Zhang, Xinmao Zhou and Wenbin Ju, 7 May 2014 B Sorbus megalocarpa at blossoming stage, 21 March 2021 C detail of the inflorescence of S. megalocarpa (B, C were taken by Tailun Hu)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.201.84027.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/708950" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">3B, C</figureCitation>
). Therefore, 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. arguta" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" rank="species" species="arguta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">S. arguta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is treated as a distinct species here following 
<bibRefCitation author="Yue, TT" editor="Yue, TT" journalOrPublisher="Science Press, Beijing" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" pagination="1 - 344" publicationUrl="http://www.iplant.cn/info/Sorbus?t=foc" refId="B18" refString="Yue, TT, Lu, LT, 1974. Spiraea, Dichotomanthes, Cotoneaster, Sorbus, Chaenomeles. In: Yue, TT, Ed., Flora Republicae Popularis Sinicae 36. Science Press, Beijing: 1 - 344, http://www.iplant.cn/info/Sorbus?t=foc" title="Spiraea, Dichotomanthes, Cotoneaster, Sorbus, Chaenomeles." url="http://www.iplant.cn/info/Sorbus?t=foc" volumeTitle="Flora Republicae Popularis Sinicae 36." year="1974">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Yü">Yue</normalizedToken>
and Lu (1974)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Gabrielian, E" journalOrPublisher="Academy of Sciences of the Armenian SSR, Erevan, USSR" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" refId="B3" refString="Gabrielian, E, 1978. The genus Sorbus L. in Western Asia and the Himalayas. Academy of Sciences of the Armenian SSR, Erevan, USSR" title="The genus Sorbus L. in Western Asia and the Himalayas." year="1978">Gabrielian (1978)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1139/b90-288" author="Phipps, JB" journalOrPublisher="Canadian Journal of Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" pagination="2209 - 2269" refId="B11" refString="Phipps, JB, Robertson, K, Smith, PG, Rohrer, JR, 1990. A checklist of the subfamily Maloideae Rosaceae. Canadian Journal of Botany 68 (10): 2209 - 2269, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1139/b90-288" title="A checklist of the subfamily Maloideae Rosaceae." url="https://doi.org/10.1139/b90-288" volume="68" year="1990">Phipps et al. (1990)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Lu, LT" editor="Wu, ZY" journalOrPublisher="9: Rosaceae. Science Press, Beijing; Missouri Botanical Garden Press, St. Loui" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" pagination="144 - 170" publicationUrl="http://foc.eflora.cn/content" refId="B7" refString="Lu, LT, Spongberg, SA, 2003. Sorbus Linnaeus. In: Wu, ZY, Raven, PH, Hong, DY, Eds., Flora of China, vol. 9: Rosaceae. Science Press, Beijing; Missouri Botanical Garden Press, St. Loui: 144 - 170, http://foc.eflora.cn/content" title="Sorbus Linnaeus." url="http://foc.eflora.cn/content" volumeTitle="Flora of China, vol." year="2003">Lu and Spongberg (2003)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/phytokeys.201.84027.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/708950" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" start="Figure 3" startId="F3">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="131">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">Figure 3.</emphasis>
Corymbs of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Sorbus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Sorbus arguta" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arguta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">Sorbus arguta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. megalocarpa" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" rank="species" species="megalocarpa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">S. megalocarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">A</emphasis>
flowering specimen of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Sorbus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Sorbus arguta" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arguta">
